Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @shallot{1}(thinly sliced). Trim and discard root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves. Reserve 6 whole lettuce leaves (12 leaves for 4 servings); finely chop remaining lettuce. Halve @tomato{1} lengthwise and thinly slice crosswise into half-moons.

In a #small microwave-safe bowl{}, combine shallot, @red wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{1/4%tsp}. Microwave until shallot turns pink, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{a drizzle} in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @shawarma spice blend{1%tbsp}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Carefully drain any excess grease from pan.

While beef cooks, in a #second small bowl{}, whisk together @yogurt{2%tbsp}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, and remaining garlic powder. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Fill lettuce leaves with shredded lettuce, beef, tomato, and pickled shallot (draining first).

Divide lettuce wraps between #plates{} and drizzle with as much white sauce as you like. Serve.

> Ground meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.